        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the first step to increasing protein from 80g per day?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The most practical first step is adding one high-protein anchor to each meal you're already eating — an extra egg at breakfast, Greek yogurt alongside lunch, or a larger protein portion at dinner. Getting from 80g to 100g is the first meaningful milestone and is achievable without overhauling your diet."
        }
      }
    ]
