      <h2>The Hard Truth</h2>
      <p>80 grams of protein a day is where most men over 40 actually are — and it's <strong>not enough to preserve muscle mass</strong>. It's not a bad diet. It's not an unhealthy lifestyle. It just doesn't meet the threshold your body needs after 40 to hold on to the muscle you've spent decades building.</p>
