    <p>Any two of those swaps gets you from 80g to 100g. From there, see <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/what-100g-protein-looks-like/">what 100 grams of protein looks like</a> for the next step — and <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/what-120g-protein-looks-like/">what 120 grams of protein looks like</a> for the full muscle preservation baseline.</p>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p><strong>You don't need to get to 120g tomorrow.</strong> Getting from 80g to 100g consistently is the first meaningful milestone — and it's already a significant improvement over where most untracked men are. Build the habit at 100g first. The number climbs from there.</p>
